headline: Does Ingersoll Rand Still Offer Value After Strong Multi Year Share Price Gains?
summary: If you have been wondering whether Ingersoll Rand at around $78.85 is a bargain in hiding or a stock past its prime, this breakdown is for you. The share price has slipped 3.6% over the last week but is still up 7.0% over the past month, while longer term returns of 51.3% over 3 years and 72.2% over 5 years hint at a business that has rewarded patient holders despite a 12.9% drop year to date and a 14.5% slide over the last year.
